'''Dibromofluoromethane''' is a mixed [[halomethane]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Dibromofluoromethane solution|url=http://www.sigmaaldrich.com/catalog/product/SUPELCO/48077?lang=en&region=RU&gclid=Cj0KEQjwyN7JBRCZn7LKgb3ki8kBEiQAaLEsqvbknhJebN0tLDRiI1CoK7y7q34K9qhnkglldD4jykEaAhdx8P8HAQ|website=[[Sigma Aldrich]]|publisher=sigmaaldrich.com|accessdate=7 June 2017}}</ref> It is soluble in [[alcohol]], [[acetone]], [[benzene]] and [[chloroform]].

==Applications==
It can be used to prepare [[bromofluoromethane]] by reductive debromination with [[organotin]] hydride as [[Tributyltin|tributyltin hydride]].<ref>[http://www.freepatentsonline.com/5189229.html Debrominating dibromofluoromethane with tributyltin hydride]</ref>

==Regulations==
Its [[ozone depletion potential]] (ODP) is 1.0 and it is included in list of Class I Ozone-Depleting Substances.

