'''LRPu''' or '''low-resilience [[polyurethane]]''' is a material distinguished by an "ability to slowly return to its original shape" ([[viscosity]]).<ref name=macworld>[http://www.macworld.com/article/59448/2007/08/sleevesbrief1.html macworld covers LRPu]</ref>

The resulting [[impact resistance]] results in LRPu being used in soft [[laptop]] sleeves<ref name=macworld /> and other lightweight cases for portable electronic equipment, as an alternative to the softer [[neoprene]].

